Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

2:16 pm - Prosecuting attorney Gail Ann Prost appeared in court for the State of Wisconsin, Defendant Kara Lynn Davis appeared in court. Attorney Ann Larson appearing with the defendant. More time needed to appoint counsel in this matter.
Initial appearance scheduled for February 28, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
RE:  Possess Fentanyl with intent to deliver, on 01-07-22.

BAIL HEARING - 
Defendant in custody and appearing by video from the Manitowoc County Jail.  The State informs the Court that the defendant will be charged with the crimes of possess Fentanyl with intent to deliver, possess drug paraphernalia and keeper of drug house.  The matters are continued for initial appearance on 01-31-22 at 1:30 p.m. Br. 1.  Bail is set at $10,000.00 recognizance bond with the condition that she not possess any controlled substances unless validly prescribed.   Bail furnished and defendant is released from custody. Court orders photos and prints at MTSO.
